# Cleaned review CSVs contain embedded literal newlines inside quoted
# multi-line review_text fields (correct CSV: CRLF row separators, bare LF
# as data content). Git's line-ending normalization can't tell the two apart
# and corrupts the embedded ones on checkout when core.autocrlf=true,
# silently changing review_text's byte length out from under the
# already-computed review_length column. Disable line-ending conversion
# entirely for these files so they round-trip byte-for-byte.
*.csv -text
